hopobject.body: I'm retired best appetizer drugs Chai Lifeline and Chaiyanu, two non-profits centered around children like Chomsky, came together to give the young girl from Rehovot an all-expense paid trip to New York. She had to jump through a couple of hurdles to qualify for the trip. Her personal oncologist had to sign off on the venture. Medical staff also put Chomsky and her fellow campers through another check-up at the boarding gate on Aug. 7 to make sure the girls were healthy enough for a 10-hour journey.
